That is, in this case, the Gibbs free energy in the saturated liquid state equals that in the saturated vapor state. The Gibbs free energy is one of the four thermodynamic potentials whose partial derivatives produce all other thermodynamics state properties; its differential is formula_158. Integrating this over an isotherm from formula_159 to formula_160, noting that the pressure is the same at each endpoint, and setting the result to zero yields
